# Feature delivery (Ship Game)

## Documentation

- Keep living MVP docs in `docs/mvp/` aligned with behavior when code changes.
- For each non-trivial package, write evidence under `docs/reports/<PACKAGE_ID>/` per `docs/mvp/agent-workflow.md` (`package-spec.md`, implementer/reviewer/remediation reports, `commands-and-results.txt`, candidate commit, extension note as needed).

## Branching and merge

- Non-minor work lands on an isolated **feature branch** (or worktree), not directly on `main`.
- Merge to `main` only after reviewer **ACCEPT** and proof of completeness (exact test commands + results; manual smoke for presentation).
- Independent packages may run in parallel on **up to 4** branches; coordinate owned paths; rebase before merge when paths collide.

## Three-agent protocol (non-minor)

1. **Implementer** — implement scope only, tests, living docs, implementer report.
2. **Adversary reviewer** — read-only; falsify gates; verdict `ACCEPT` / `REMEDIATE` / `BLOCK`.
3. **Remediation** — fix findings on the same feature branch; recheck until `ACCEPT`.

Prompts and severity rules: `docs/mvp/agent-workflow.md` (Mandatory three-agent protocol).

## Minor changes

- Typos and trivial one-liners may skip the full triad but still get a short note in living docs or `docs/reports/`.

## Invariants

- Preserve deterministic fixed-step simulation and MonoGame-free Gameplay/domain logic.
- Do not weaken gates or change requirements only to pass tests.
- Contract changes need a short proposal naming affected packages and migration impact.
